To create a community event, you only need to make a post in <#1114410503029137428> or ask for interest in <#1114365926284992564> before you commit. Make sure you read the pinned guidelines before continuing and that you are IRLVerified.

Sesh events are not required to run a community event, but if you would like to make your event visible to the rest of the community or use its functionality to your benefit.

A simple Sesh event can be created by running the `/create` command in chat and specifying a title and the time the event starts. The other options are not required.

See <#1114568693565890581> for more information on the guidelines and how to use Sesh.